{
  "text": "Swine were housed four to six swine per 18-m 2 pen at the Burley-Demeritt swine facility (Lee, NH). All swine were fed a miniature swine ration (Agway, Syracuse, NY) with a caloric density of 10.21 kJ/g, formulated to meet the nutritional needs of growing miniature swine. Full-fed swine were fed 73 g \u00b7 kg body wt \u03ea1 \u00b7 day \u03ea1 in two meals; this was equivalent to the daily caloric intake of swine in our previous study [CITATION_1] . Restricted-fed swine were fed 53 g \u00b7 kg body wt \u03ea1 \u00b7 day \u03ea1 in two meals; this was \u03f325% less than the full-fed swine and [CITATION_2] ",
  "correct_citation": {
